---
description: Handle uncertainty by clarifying or planning first
alwaysApply: true
---

# Clarify Before Coding

If there is meaningful uncertainty about requirements, constraints, or expected behavior, do not implement immediately.

- Ask focused clarifying question(s) first, or
- Propose a short implementation plan and request confirmation.

Only start implementation after the uncertainty is resolved or the plan is approved.

When uncertainty appears during implementation, pause and re-confirm before continuing.
